# AI/ML Internship – Day 6

## Topic

AI Project Workflow & Lightweight Open-Source LLM Research

## What I Learned

* Understood the end-to-end AI project development workflow.
* Learned how to analyze a problem statement and gather project requirements.
* Explored the process of selecting suitable algorithms and AI models based on project needs.
* Studied data architecture and system architecture planning.
* Learned the importance of model evaluation, optimization, testing, and deployment planning.
* Started researching lightweight open-source Large Language Models (LLMs) for real-world AI applications.
* Understood how different AI tasks may require different LLMs depending on performance, latency, and resource constraints.

## Key Takeaway

A well-planned AI project begins with understanding the problem, designing the right architecture, selecting the appropriate model, and validating it before deployment.
